---
title: Italian Chicken & Pepper Sandos with Potato Wedges & Tangy Garlic Sauce
description: What’s not to love about the classic hoagie (or sub, or grinder, or wedge) filled with tender meat, melty cheese, and lightly charred veggies? We’ll wait. This version boasts herby, Italian-seasoned chicken, sautéed pepper and onion, gooey mozzarella, and a creamy garlic sauce. It’s all stuffed inside garlic butter baguettes and served with golden brown potato wedges for a dinner that’ll have you head over heels at first bite.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6075d61c38625b79a415ba8b-77fffbc9.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/italian-chicken-pepper-sandos-6075d61c38625b79a415ba8b-f94c643b.pdf
author: Michelle Doll Olson
cuisine: Italian
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/italian-chicken-pepper-sandos-6075d61c38625b79a415ba8b
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 1110 kcal
  fat: 58 g
  saturated fat: 21 g
  carbohydrates: 104 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 48 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 1200 mg
---

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @Yellow Onion{1}. Halve, core, and thinly slice @Long Green Pepper{1} into strips.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until golden brown and crispy, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, and half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest later). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add onion and green pepper; cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and lightly browned, ~{5-7%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}.

While veggies cook, in a second #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @butter{2%tablespoon} and remaining garlic powder; microwave until butter is just softened, ~{10-15%seconds}. Stir to combine and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}; set aside.

Slice @demi-baguette{2} lengthwise, stopping before you get all the way through; spread garlic butter onto cut sides. Place cut sides up on a second baking sheet.

Toast on middle rack until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}.

While garlic buns toast, pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with paper towels; season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in pan used for veggies over medium-high heat. Add chicken and @Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon}; cook, stirring, until chicken is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1} and @water{2%tablespoon}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Return cooked veggies to pan; stir to combine. Turn off heat.

Spread bottom halves of toasted garlic buns with half the garlic sauce. Top with chicken and veggie mixture, then sprinkle with @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}. Return to middle rack until cheese melts, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Divide sandos and potatoes between plates. Serve with remaining garlic sauce on the side.

